This is the code for the paper:

"Exploring Cross-domain Consistency for Composed Query Image Retrieval" Submission to CVPR ID 7022

(1) FashionIQ:
Creat files "dress","shirt", and "toptee" to save the outputs.
dress: python train.py --dataset fashioniq --name dress --max_decay_epoch 20 --img_weight 1.0 --class_weight 1.0 --mul_kl_weight 1.0 --model_dir ./dress --num_epochs 50
shirt: python train.py --dataset fashioniq --name shirt  --max_decay_epoch 20 --img_weight 1.0 --class_weight 1.0 --mul_kl_weight 1.0 --model_dir ./shirt --num_epochs 50
toptee: python train.py --dataset fashioniq --name toptee  --max_decay_epoch 20 --img_weight 1.0 --class_weight 1.0 --mul_kl_weight 1.0 --model_dir ./toptee --num_epochs 50

(2) Shoes:
Creat files "shoes" to save the outputs.
python train.py --dataset shoes  --max_decay_epoch 30 --img_weight 1.0 --class_weight 1.0 --mul_kl_weight 1.0 --model_dir ./shoes --num_epochs 50

(3) Fashion200K:
Creat files "Fashion200k" to save the outputs.
python train.py --dataset fashion200k  --img_weight 1.0 --class_weight 1.0 --mul_kl_weight 1.0 --model_dir ./fashion200k --num_epochs 40

The pre-trained models are stored in the following URLs. ``https://anonymous.4open.science/r/Test-C02F''.
